obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8742)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8742&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Street`
  line `Vendors (Protection of Livelihood and Regulation of Street Vending) Act, 2014.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different States and any reference in`
  line `any provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed in relation to any State as a reference`
  line `to the coming into force of that provision in that State.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Act shall not apply to any land, premises and trains owned and controlled`
  line `by the Railways under the Railway Act, 1989 (24 of 1989).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 1.--In sub-section (2), omit 'except the State of Jammu and Kashmir'.`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second`
  line `Order, 2020, Notification No. S.O. 3465(E), dated (5-10-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh`
  line `Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated`
  line `(23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st May, 2014, vide notification No. S.O. 1185 (E), dated 1st May, 2014, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8743)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8743&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) appropriate Government means in respect of matters relating to,--`
  line
  line `(i) a Union territory without Legislature, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Union territories with Legislature, the Government of the National Capital Territory`
  line `of Delhi or, as the case may be, the Government of Union territory of Puducherry;`
  line
  line `(iii) a State, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) holding capacity means the maximum number of street vendors who can in any vending`
  line `zone and has been determined as such by the local authority on the commendations of the Town`
  line `Vending Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) local authority means a Municipal Corporation or a Municipal Council or a Nagar`
  line `Panchayat, by whatever name called, or the Cantonment Board, or as the case may be, a civil area`
  line `committee appointed under section 47 of the Cantonment Act, 2006(41 of 2006)or such other body`
  line `entitled to function as a local authority in any city or town to provide civic services and regulate street`
  line `vending and includes the planning authority which regulates the land use in that city or town;`
  line
  line `(d) mobile vendors means street vendors who carry out vending activities in designated area by`
  line `moving from one place to another place vending their goods and services;`
  line
  line `(e) natural market means a market where sellers and buyers have traditionally congregated for`
  line `the sale and purchase of products or services and has been determine das such by the local authority`
  line `on the recommendations of the Town Vending Committee;`
  line
  line `(f) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the term notify shall`
  line `be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(g) planning authority means an Urban Development Authority or any other authority in any`
  line `city or town designated by the appropriate Government as responsible for regulating the land use by defining the precise extent of areas for any particular activity in the master plan or development plan`
  line `or zonal plan or layout plan or any other spatial plan which is legally enforceable under the applicable`
  line `Town and Country Planning Act or the Urban Development Act or the Municipal Act, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(i) Schedule means the Schedule annexed to this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) scheme means a scheme framed by the appropriate Government under section 38;`
  line
  line `(k) stationary vendors means street vendors who carry out vending activities on regular basis at`
  line `a specific location;`
  line
  line `(l) street vendor means a person engaged in vending of articles, goods, wares, food items or`
  line `merchandise of everyday use or offering services to the general public, in a street, lane, sidewalk,`
  line `footpath, pavement, public park or any other public place or private area, from a temporary built up`
  line `structure or by moving from place to place and includes hawker, peddler, squatter and all other`
  line `synonymous terms which may be local or region specific; and the words street vending with their`
  line `grammatical variations and cognate expressions, shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(m) Town Vending Committee means the body constituted by the appropriate Government`
  line `under section 22;`
  line
  line `(n) vending zone means an area or a place or a location designated as such by the local`
  line `authority, on the recommendations of the Town Vending Committee, for the specific use by street`
  line `vendors for street vending and includes footpath, side walk, pavement, embankment, portions of a`
  line `street, waiting area for public or any such place considered suitable for vending activities and`
  line `providing services to the general public.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any enactment or any provision thereof, shall, in relation to an area in`
  line `which such enactment or such provision is not in force be construed as a reference to the corresponding`
  line `law, if any, in force in that area.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line
  line `Section 2.--In sub-section (1), in clause (a), in sub-clause (ii), after "the Government of the National`
  line `Capital Territory of Delhi", insert "the Government of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir"`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second`
  line `Order, 2020, Notification No. S.O. 3465(E), dated (5-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8744)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Survey of street vendors and protection from eviction or relocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8744&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Town Vending`
  line `Committee shall, within such period and in such manner as may be specified in the scheme, conduct a`
  line `survey of all existing street vendors, within the area under its jurisdiction, and subsequent survey shall be`
  line `carried out at least once in every five years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Town Vending Committee shall ensure that all existing street vendors, identified in the`
  line `survey, are accommodated in the vending zones subject to a norm conforming to two and half per cent. of`
  line `the population of the ward or zone or town or city, as the case may be, in accordance with the plan for`
  line `street vending and the holding capacity of the vending zones.`
  line
  line `(3) No street vendor shall be evicted or, as the case may be, relocated till the survey specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) has been completed and the certificate of vending is issued to all street vendors.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8745)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Issue of certificate of vending.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8745&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every street vendor, identified under the survey carried out`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3, who has completed the age of fourteen years or such age as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government, shall be issued a certificate of vending by the Town Vending`
  line `Committee, subject to such terms and conditions and within the period specified in the scheme including`
  line `the restrictions specified in the plan for street vending:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person, whether or not included under the survey under sub-section (1) of section 3,`
  line `who has been issued a certificate of vending before the commencement of this Act, whether known as`
  line `licence or any other form of permission (whether as a stationary vendor or a mobile vendor or under any other category) shall be deemed to be a street vendor for that category for the period for which he has`
  line `been issued such certificate of vending.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in the intervening period between two surveys, any person seeks to vend, the Town`
  line `Vending Committee may grant a certificate of vending to such person, subject to the scheme, the plan for`
  line `street vending and the holding capacity of the vending zones.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the number of street vendors identified under sub-section (1) or the number of persons`
  line `seeking to vend under sub-section (2) are more than the holding capacity of the vending zone and exceeds`
  line `the number of persons to be accommodated in that vending zone, the Town Vending Committee shall`
  line `carry out a draw of lots for issuing the certificate of vending for that vending zone and the remaining`
  line `persons shall be accommodated in any adjoining vending zone to avoid relocation.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8746)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Conditions for issue of certificate of vending.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8746&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every street vendor shall give an undertaking`
  line `to the Town Vending Committee prior to the issue of a certificate of vending under section 4, that—`
  line
  line `(a) he shall carry on the business of street vending himself or through any of his family member;`
  line
  line `(b) he has no other means of livelihood:`
  line
  line `(c) he shall not transfer in any manner whatsoever, including rent, the certificate of vending or the`
  line `place specified therein to any other person.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a street vendor to whom a certificate of vending is issued dies or suffers from any`
  line `permanent disability or is ill, one of his family member in following order of priority, may vend in his`
  line `place, till the validity of the certificate of vending—`
  line
  line `(a) spouse of the street vendor;`
  line
  line `(b) dependent child of the street vendor:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a dispute arises as to who is entitled to vend in the place of the vendor, the matter`
  line `shall be decided by the committee under section 20.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8747)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Categories of certificate of vending and issue of identity cards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8747&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The certificate of vending`
  line `shall be issued under any of the following categories, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a stationary vendor;`
  line
  line `(b) a mobile vendor; or`
  line
  line `(c) any other category as may be specified in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate of vending issued for the categories specified in sub-section (1) shall be in such`
  line `form, and issued in such manner, as may be specified in the scheme and specify the vending zone where`
  line `the street vendor shall carry on his vending activities, the days and timings for carrying on such vending`
  line `activities and the conditions and restriction subject to which he shall carry on such vending activities.`
  line
  line `(3) Every street vendor who has been issued certificate of vending under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `issued identity cards in such form and manner as may be specified in the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8748)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Criteria for issuing certificate of vending.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8748&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The criteria to be followed by the Town Vending`
  line `Committee for issuing certificate of vending to a street vendor shall be as specified in the scheme, which`
  line `may, apart from other things, provide for preference to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, Other`
  line `Backward Classes, women, persons with disabilities, minorities or such other categories as may be`
  line `specified in the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8749)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vending fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8749&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every street vendor who has been issued certificate of vending shall pay such`
  line `vending fees as may be specified in the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8750)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Validity and renewal of certificate of vending.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8750&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every certificate of vending shall be valid`
  line `for such period as may be specified in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) Every certificate of vending shall be renewable for such period, in such manner, and on payment`
  line `of such fees, as may be specified in the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8751)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Cancellation or suspension of certificate of vending.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8751&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where a street vendor who has been`
  line `issued a certificate of vending under this Act commits breach of any of the conditions thereof or any other`
  line `terms and conditions specified or the purpose of regulating street vending under this Act or any rules or`
  line `schemes made thereunder, or where the Town Vending Committee is satisfied that such certificate of`
  line `vending has been secured by the street vendor through misrepresentation or fraud, the Town Vending`
  line `Committee may, without prejudice to any other fine which may have been incurred by the street vendor`
  line `under this Act, cancel the certificate of vending or suspend the same in such as may be specified in the`
  line `scheme and for such period as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such cancellation or suspension shall be made by the Town Vending Committee`
  line `unless an opportunity of hearing has been given to the street vendor.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8752)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appeal from decision of Town Vending Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8752&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who is aggrieved by any`
  line `decision of the Town Vending Committee with respect to issue of certificate of vending under section 6`
  line `or cancellation or suspension of certificate of vending under section 10 may prefer an appeal to the local`
  line `authority in such form, within such period, and in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be disposed of by the local authority unless the appellant has been given an`
  line `opportunity of hearing.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (8753)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Rights of street vendor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8753&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every street vendor shall have the right to carry on the business of`
  line `street vending activities in accordance with the terms and conditions mentioned in the certificate of`
  line vending.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any area or space, as the case may`
  line `be, has been earmarked as no-vending zone, no street vendor shall carry out any vending activities in that`
  line zone.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (8754)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Right of street vendor for a new site or area on relocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8754&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every street vendor, who`
  line `possesses a certificate of vending, shall, in case of his relocation under section 18, be entitled for new site`
  line `or area, as the case may be, for carrying out his vending activities as may be determined by the local`
  line `authority, in consultation with the Town Vending Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8755)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Duty of street vendors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8755&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where a street vendor occupies space on a time sharing basis, he shall`
  line `remove his goods and wares every day at the end of the time-sharing period allowed to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8756)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Maintenance of cleanliness and public hygiene.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8756&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every street vendor shall maintain cleanliness`
  line `and public hygiene in the vending zones and the adjoining areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8757)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Maintenance of civic amenities in vending zone in good condition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8757&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Every street vendor shall`
  line `maintain civic amenities and public property in the vending zone in good condition and not damage or`
  line `destroy or cause any damage or destruction to the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8758)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Payment of maintenance charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8758&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every street vendor shall pay such periodic maintenance`
  line `charges for the civic amenities and facilities provided in the vending zones as may be determined by the`
  line `local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8759)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Relocation or eviction of street vendors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8759&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The local authority may, on the recommendations`
  line `of the Town Vending Committee, declare a zone or part of it to be a no-vending zone for any public`
  line `purpose and relocate the street vendors vending in that area, in such manner as may be specified in the`
  line scheme.
  line
  line `(2) The local authority shall evict such street vendor whose certificate of vending has been cancelled`
  line `under section 10 or who does not have a certificate of vending and vends without such certificate, in such`
  line `manner as may be specified in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) No street vendor shall be relocated or evicted by the local authority from the place specified in the`
  line `certificate of vending unless he has been given thirty days' notice for the same in such manner as may be`
  line `specified in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) A street vendor shall be relocated or evicted by the local authority physically in such manner as`
  line `may be specified in the scheme only after he had failed to vacate the place specified in the certificate of`
  line `vending, after the expiry of the period specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(5) Every street vendor who fails to relocate or vacate the place specified in the certificate of vending,`
  line `after the expiry of the period specified in the notice, shall be liable to pay for every day of such default, a`
  line `penalty which may extend up to two hundred and fifty rupees, as may be determined by the local`
  line `authority, but shall not be more than the value of goods seized.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8760)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Seizure and reclaiming of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8760&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the street vendor fails to vacate the place specified in`
  line `the certificate of vending, after the lapse of the period specified in the notice given under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 18, the local authority, in addition to evicting the street vendor under section 18, may, if it`
  line `deems necessary, seize the goods of such street vendor in such manner as may be specified in the scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such seizure is carried out, a list of goods seized shall be prepared, as`
  line `specified in the scheme, and a copy thereof, duly signed by the person authorised to seize the goods, shall`
  line `be issued to the street vendor.`
  line
  line `(2) The street vendor whose goods have been seized under sub-section (1) may, reclaim his goods in`
  line `such manner, and after paying such fees, as may be specified in the scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of non-perishable goods, the local authority shall release the goods within two`
  line `working days of the claim being made by the street vendor and in case of perishable goods the local`
  line `authority shall release the goods on the same day of the claim being made by the street vendor.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8761)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Redressal of grievances or resolution of disputes of street vendors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8761&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate`
  line `Government may constitute one or more committees consisting of a Chairperson who has been a civil`
  line `judge or a judicial magistrate and two other professional shaving such experience as may be prescribed`
  line `for the purpose of deciding the applications received under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that no employee of the appropriate Government or the local authority shall be appointed as`
  line `members of the committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Every street vendor who has a grievance or dispute may make an application in writing to the`
  line `committee constituted under sub-section (1) in such form and manner as maybe prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of grievance or dispute under sub-section (2), the committee referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) shall, after verification and enquiry in such manner, as may be prescribed, take steps for redressal of`
  line `such grievance or resolution of such dispute, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who is aggrieved by the decision of the committee may prefer an appeal to the local`
  line `authority in such form, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The local authority shall dispose of the appeal received under sub-section (4) within such time and`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the local authority shall, before disposing of the appeal, give an opportunity of being`
  line `heard to the aggrieved person.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8762)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Plan for street vending.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8762&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every local authority shall, in consultation with the planning`
  line `authority and on the recommendations of the Town Vending Committee, once in every five years, prepare`
  line `a plan to promote the vocation of street vendors covering the matters contained in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The plan for street vending prepared by the local authority shall be submitted to the appropriate`
  line `Government for approval and that Government shall, before notifying the plan, determine the norms`
  line `applicable to the street vendors.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8763)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Town Vending Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8763&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by rules made in this behalf,`
  line `provide for the term and the manner of constituting a Town Vending Committee in each local authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may, if considers necessary, provide for constitution of`
  line `more than one Town Vending Committee, or a Town Vending Committee for each zone or ward, in each`
  line `local authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Town Vending Committee shall consist of:—`
  line
  line `(a) Municipal Commissioner or Chief Executive Officer, as the case may be, who shall be the`
  line `Chairperson; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other members as may be prescribed, to be nominated by the appropriate`
  line `Government, representing the local authority, medical officer of the local authority, the planning`
  line `authority, traffic police, police, association of street vendors, market associations, traders`
  line `associations, non-governmental organisations, community based organisations, resident welfare`
  line `associations, banks and such other interests as it deems proper;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of members nominated to represent the non-governmental organisations and the`
  line `community based organisations shall not be less than ten per cent.;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of members representing the street vendors shall not be less than forty per cent.`
  line `who shall be elected by the street vendors themselves in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that one-third of members representing the street vendors shall be from amongst women`
  line `vendors:`
  line
  line `Provided further that due representation shall be given to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes,`
  line `Other Backward Classes, minorities and persons with disabilities from amongst the members representing`
  line `street vendors.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson and the members nominated under sub-section (2) shall receive such allowances`
  line `as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8764)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Meetings of Town Vending Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8764&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Town Vending Committee shall meet at such`
  line `times and places within the jurisdiction of the local authority and shall observe such rules of procedure in`
  line `regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, and discharge such functions, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every decision of the Town Vending Committee shall be notified along with the reasons for`
  line `taking such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8765)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Temporary association of persons with Town Vending Committee for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8765&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Town Vending Committee may associate with itself in such manner and for such`
  line `purposes, as may be prescribed, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire, in carrying out any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated under sub-section (1) shall be paid such allowances as maybe prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8766)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Office space and other employees for Town Vending Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8766&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The local authority shall`
  line `provide the Town Vending Committee with appropriate office space and such employees as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8767)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Publication of street vendor’s charter and data-base and carrying out of social audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8767&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every Town Vending Committee shall publish the street vendor's charter specifying therein the time`
  line `within which the certificate of vending shall be issued to a street vendor and the time within which such`
  line `certificate of vending shall be renewed and other activities to be performed within the time limit specified`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(2) Every Town Vending Committee shall maintain up to date records of registered street vendors and`
  line `street vendors to whom certificate of vending has been issued containing name of such street vendor, stall`
  line `allotted to him, nature of business carried out by him, category of street vending and such other`
  line `particulars which may be relevant to the street vendors, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Town Vending Committee shall carry out social audit of its activities under the Act or the`
  line `rules or the schemes made there under in such form and manner as may be specified in the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8768)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Prevention of harassment by police and other authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8768&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, no street vendor who carries on the street vending`
  line `activities in accordance with the terms and conditions of his certificate of vending shall be prevented from`
  line `exercising such rights by any person or police or any other authority exercising powers under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (8769)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalty for contraventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8769&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If any street vendor—`
  line
  line `(a) indulges in vending activities without a certificate of vending;`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes the terms of certificate of vending; or`
  line
  line `(c) contravenes any other terms and conditions specified for the purpose of regulating street`
  line `vending under this Act or any rules or schemes made thereunder,`
  line
  line `he shall be liable to a penalty for each such offence which may extend up to rupees two thousand as may`
  line `be determined by the local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (8770)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Provisions of this Act, not to be construed as conferring ownership rights, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8770&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing`
  line `contained in this Act shall be construed as conferring upon a street vendor any temporary, permanent or`
  line `perpetual right of carrying out vending activities in the vending zones allotted to him or in respect of any`
  line `place on which he carries on such vending activity.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to any stationery vendor, if a temporary leasehold`
  line `or ownership right has been conferred on him by a lease deed or otherwise, in respect of a place at`
  line `specific location where he carries on such vending activity in accordance with the provisions of any law`
  line `for the time being in force for carrying out such vending activity.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (8771)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8771&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every Town Vending Committee shall furnish, from time to time, to the appropriate`
  line `Government and the local authority such returns as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (8772)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Promotional measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8772&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, in consultation with the Town`
  line `Vending Committee, local authority, planning authority and street vendors associations or unions, undertake promotional measures of making available credit, insurance and other welfare schemes of social security`
  line `for the street vendors.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (8773)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Research, training and awareness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8773&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, to the extent of`
  line `availability of financial and other resources,—`
  line
  line `(a) organise capacity building programmes to enable the street vendors to exercise the rights`
  line `contemplated under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) undertake research, education and training programmes to advance knowledge and`
  line `understanding of the role of the informal sector in the economy, in general and the street vendors, in`
  line `particular and to raise awareness among the public through Town Vending Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (8774)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8774&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything in consistent there in contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (8775)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Powers to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8775&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, by general or special order in writing,`
  line `delegate such of its powers and functions under this Act (excluding the power to frame scheme under`
  line `section 38 and power to make rules under section 36), as it may deem necessary, to the local authority or`
  line `the Town Vending Committee or any other officer, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified`
  line `in that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (8776)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8776&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the recommendations made by the appropriate Government`
  line `or otherwise, if the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, amend the Schedules and thereupon the First Schedule or the Second Schedule, as the case`
  line `may be, shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after it is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (8777)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8777&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall, within one year from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the age for street vending under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the form, period and manner of filing appeal with the local authority under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the persons and the experience such person shall have under sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and the manner of making application under sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of verification and enquiry on receipt of grievance or dispute, the time within`
  line `which and the manner in which steps for redressal of grievances and resolution of disputes may be`
  line `taken under sub-section (3) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) the form, the time within which and the manner in which an appeal may be filed under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(g) the time within which and the manner in which an appeal shall be disposed of under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(h) the term of, and the manner of constituting, the Town Vending Committee under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(i) the number of other members of the Town Vending Committee under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of elections among street vendors under clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(k) the allowances to Chairperson and members under sub-section (3) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(l) the time and place for meeting, procedure for transaction of business at meetings and functions`
  line `to be discharged by the Town Vending Committee under section 23;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner and the purpose for which a person may be associated under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 24;`
  line
  line `(n) the allowances to be paid to an associated person under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(o) the other employees of Town Vending Committee under section 25;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of maintaining up to date record of all street vendors under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(q) the returns to be furnished under section 30;`
  line
  line `(r) the manner of publishing summary of scheme under sub-section (2) of section 38.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule and scheme made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session ,for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or scheme or both Houses agree that the rule or scheme`
  line `should not be made, the rule or scheme shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule or scheme made by the State Government under this Act shall, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, be laid before each House of the State Legislature where there are two Houses, and where`
  line `there is one House of the State Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (8778)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8778&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act or any rule or scheme made`
  line `thereunder, the local authority may make bye-laws to provide for all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation and manner of vending in restriction-free-vending zones, restricted-vending`
  line `zones and designated vending zones;`
  line
  line `(b) determination of monthly maintenance charges for the civic amenities and facilities in the`
  line `vending zones under section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) determination of penalty under sub-section (5) of section 18 and section 28;`
  line
  line `(d) the regulation of the collection of taxes and fees in the vending zones;`
  line
  line `(e) the regulation of traffic in the vending zones;`
  line
  line `(f) the regulation of the quality of products and services provided to the public in vending zones`
  line `and maintenance of public health, hygiene and safety standards;`
  line
  line `(g) the regulation of civic services in the vending zones; and`
  line
  line `(h) the regulation of such other matters in the vending zones as may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (8779)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Scheme for street vendors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8779&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the appropriate Government shall`
  line `frame a scheme, within six months from the date of commencement of this Act, after due consultations`
  line `with the local authority and the Town Vending Committee, by notification, which may specify all or any`
  line `of the matters provided in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) A summary of the scheme notified by the appropriate Government under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `published by the local authority in at least two local newspapers in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (8780)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761&sectionId=8780&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_47_83_00001_201407_1517807327761
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not in consistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
